{"id":41987,"category_id":1,"owner":"BBC","created_at":"17/03/2012","title":"زيارة غير مجانية","pictures":"//wscdn.bbc.co.uk/worldservice/assets/images/2012/03/16/120316162641_xtra_bin_640x360_bbc.jpg","active":1,"views":103,"content":"يدور جدل في بريطانيا حول مخطط لجعل زائري بيغ بين يدفعون رسوما لزيارتها. وقالت السلطات في مجلس العموم البريطاني إنه من المهم بمكان تغطية تكاليف الصيانة. ولكن بعض أعضاء البرلمان وصفوا هذه الخطوة بأنها مخزية ودعوا إلى مناقشة الموضوع. المزيد في تقرير Alan Soady من البي بي سي. \r\nAn argument has broken out in the UK over plans to make visitors pay to tour Big Ben. The House of Commons authorities say it's necessary to cover costs. But some members of the Parliament are describing the move as \"disgraceful\" and have called a debate on the issue. Alan Soady reports .FOR THE BBC \r\nIt's one of the must-see attractions for visitors to London. Most tourists only get to look at the outside of the famous clock tower. But for a few thousand people a year who organise a tour of it, THIS is how it sounds on the inside... The clanking of the old machinery which operates the clock and those bongs. \r\nIt can only be visited if it's arranged in advance by contacting a member of Parliament, usually only done by the small number of UK residents who areaware of it. \r\nBut rather than those tours being free in future, there'll be a charge of fifteen pounds per person. House of Commons officials say it will simply cover the 111-thousand pounds a year it costs to provide the tours. \r\nBut a group of disgruntled MPs argue that UK residents already pay through their taxes. They say Big Ben is a world-renowned symbol of British democracy, and visiting it should be free. \r\nما هو أكثر معلم سياحي مثير زرتموه؟\r\nmust-see \r\nلا يجب تفويت فرصة رؤيته \r\nclock tower \r\nبرج الساعة \r\ntour \r\nيتجول \r\nclanking \r\nالصوت الذي تصدره الآلات \r\nbongs \r\nصوت دقات الجرس \r\nin advance \r\nمسبقا \r\nare aware \r\nيدركون \r\ncharge \r\nيدفع \r\ndisgruntled \r\nمس